HEADWORD: Reconvention
<hw>Re`con*ven"tion</hw> <pr>(-v?n"sh?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Civil
Law)</fld> <def>A cross demand; an action brought by the defendant
against the plaintiff before the same judge.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.
Bouvier.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

